description: {"blocks":[{"key":"el7uu","text":"This protocol describes how to prepare thin, fixed mouse brain tissue sections from whole fixed mouse brains in preparation for immunohistochemistry or histology. This process includes immersion fixation and cryoprotection of mouse brains, followed by flash freezing of whole brains and cryosectioning into thin tissue sections using a freezing microtome.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
